  <h1 class="font-weight-bold text-center text-info">
MEET THE POLLINATORS
</h1>
<hr class="my-4">
<h6>Birds, bats, bees, butterflies, beetles, and other small mammals that pollinate plants are responsible for
  bringing us one out of every three bites of food. They also sustain our ecosystems and produce our natural
  resources by helping plants reproduce. Pollinating animals travel from plant to plant carrying pollen on their
  bodies in a vital interaction that allows the transfer of genetic material critical to the reproductive system
  of most flowering plants â€“ the very plants that bring us food, prevent soil erosion and
  increase carbon sequestration. Learn about these important pollinators below!
</div>
</div>

  <!-- images -->
<p>  <div class="row mt-4">
  <!-- butterfly -->
  <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-3">
    <div class="card mb-3">
      <div class="img-max">
    <img src="/butterfly.PNG" class="card-img-top" alt="Butterfly">
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <p class="card-text"></div>
    <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
        <li class="list-group-item list-group-item-success">Butterflies are found on every continent but Antarctica; the U.S.
          is home to about 700 different species.</li>
  <li class="list-group-item">Butterflies are diurnal, pollinating a wide variety of flowers that open during the day. </li>
  <li class="list-group-item list-group-item-success"> They can see red, their favorite color, while bees cannot.</li>
</ul>
<div class="card-body">
<%= link_to "Learn More", "http://pollinator.org", target:"_blank", class:"card-link" %>
</div>
  </div>
  </div>

  <!-- bee -->
  <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-3">
    <div class="card mb-3">
        <div class="img-max">
    <img src="/bee.PNG" class="card-img-top" alt="Bee">
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <p class="card-text"></div>
    <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
  <li class="list-group-item list-group-item-success">There are 4000 bee species in the U.S. There are 450 species New York State.</li>
  <li class="list-group-item">Globally, 81 million hives produce 1.6 million tonnes of honey, around a third of
    which is traded across national borders.</li>
  <li class="list-group-item list-group-item-success">Some crops, including blueberries and cherries, are 90 percent
    dependent on honey bee pollination.</li>
</ul>
<div class="card-body">
<%= link_to "Learn More", "http://pollinator.org", target:"_blank", class:"card-link" %>
</div>
</div>
  </div>

  <!-- hummingbird -->
  <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-3">
    <div class="card mb-3">
        <div class="img-max">
    <img src="/hummingbird.PNG" class="card-img-top" alt="Hummingbird">
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <p class="card-text"></div>
    <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
  <li class="list-group-item list-group-item-success">There are more than 300 species of hummingbirds in the world,
    all of which are found only in the western hemisphere.</li>
  <li class="list-group-item">Hummingbirds lap up nectar with their tongues rather than use their beak as a straw</li>
  <li class="list-group-item list-group-item-success">They feed on nectar, eat insects and obtain tree sap from sap wells</li>
</ul>
<div class="card-body">
<%= link_to "Learn More", "http://pollinator.org", target:"_blank", class:"card-link" %>
</div>
</div>
  </div>

  <!-- bat -->
  <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-3">
    <div class="card mb-3">
        <div class="img-max">
    <img src="/bat.PNG" class="card-img-top" alt="Bat">
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <p class="card-text"></div>
    <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
      <li class="list-group-item list-group-item-success">Flowers produce a musty, rotten odor to attract bats</li>
      <li class="list-group-item">Some bats use echolocation to find flowers</li>
      <li class="list-group-item list-group-item-success">Bats service many plants that we use for medicinal, cultural and economic purposes</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="card-body">
<%= link_to "Learn More", "http://pollinator.org", target:"_blank", class:"card-link" %>
</div>
